The city was informed early by the management about the intention.
"We have of course offered our help to the company," Korwisi said.
However, the friendly contacts could not have changed the difficulties of the computer manufacturer with the landlord of the property at Marienbader Platz.
Ultimately, economic reasons would have been the decisive factor.
Now it is a matter of preventing a long vacancy in such a prominent place.
“I hope the owner and landlord of the building is cooperative.”
