Still, Edmond Mulet, the head of the U.N. mission in Haiti, described the election "as quite good in many respects."
According to a cautious statement from observers from the Organization of American States and the Caribbean Community, "these irregularities, however serious they may be, do not necessarily invalidate the process."
In other words, the show goes on.
