It is not known whether Fernández will be politically active even without the support of her husband after the end of her term.
If so, it needs the support of the middle class, which has largely had enough of Kirchnerism.
When the Argentines return from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy that has been brought to her will have ebbed.
If she wants to win another election, she has to decide whether to quietly overturn many of her husband's political decisions.
